1 On page 1 of the printed A-engrossed bill, line 2, after “use” insert “;
2 creating new provisions” and after “53,” insert “54,”.
3 On page 4, after line 27, insert:
4 “SECTION 6. Section 54, chapter 110, Oregon Laws 2024, is amended to
5 read:
6 “Sec. 54. (1) After the deadline for submission of applications established
7 under section [55 of this 2024 Act] 53, chapter 110, Oregon Laws 2024, the
8 city shall:
9 “(a) Review applications filed for compliance with sections 49 to 59,
10 chapter 110, Oregon Laws 2024 [of this 2024 Act].
11 “(b) For each completed application that complies with sections 49 to
12 59, chapter 110, Oregon Laws 2024 [of this 2024 Act], provide notice to the
13 residents of the proposed site area who were not signatories to the applica-
14 tion.
15 “(c) Provide opportunities for public participation in selecting a site, in-
16 cluding, at least:
17 “(A) One public comment period;
18 “(B)(i) One meeting of the city’s planning commission at which public
19 testimony is considered;
20 “(ii) One meeting of the city’s council at which public testimony is con-
21 sidered; or

1 “(iii) One public open house; and
2 “(C) Notice on the city’s website or published in a paper of record at least
3 14 days before:
4 “(i) A meeting under subparagraph (B) of this paragraph; and
5 “(ii) The beginning of a comment period under subparagraph (A) of this
6 paragraph.
7 “(d) Consult with, request necessary information from and provide the
8 opportunity for written comment from:
9 “(A) The owners of each lot or parcel within the site;
10 “(B) If the city does not currently exercise land use jurisdiction over the
11 entire site, the governing body of each county with land use jurisdiction over
12 the site;
13 “(C) Any special district that provides urban services to the site; and
14 “(D) Any public or private utility that provides utilities to the site.
15 “(2) An application filed under this section must:
16 “(a) Be completed for each property owner or group of property owners
17 that are proposing an urban growth boundary amendment under sections 49
18 to 59, chapter 110, Oregon Laws 2024 [of this 2024 Act];
19 “(b) Be in writing in a form and format as required by the city;
20 “(c) Specify the lots or parcels that are the subject of the application;
21 “(d) Be signed by all owners of lots or parcels included within the appli-
22 cation; and
23 “(e) Include each owner’s signed consent to annexation of the properties
24 if the site is added to the urban growth boundary.
25 “(3) If the city has received approval from all property owners of such
26 lands, in writing in a form and format specified by the city, the governing
27 body of the city may select an application and the city shall adopt a con-
28 ceptual plan as described in section 55, chapter 110, Oregon Laws 2024,
29 [of this 2024 Act] for all or a portion of the lands contained within the ap-
30 plication.
