9 On page 7, delete lines 16 through 40 and insert:
10 “SECTION 10. Section 11 of this 2026 Act is added to and made a
11 part of sections 49 to 59, chapter 110, Oregon Laws 2024.
12 “SECTION 11. (1) The City of Woodburn, when adding a site to the
13 city’s urban growth boundary under sections 49 to 59, chapter 110,
14 Oregon Laws 2024:
15 “(a) Is not required to comply with the selection conditions in sec-
16 tion 50 (1)(b)(D)(ii) or (iii), chapter 110, Oregon Laws 2024.
17 “(b) Is not required to solicit submission of applications or other-
18 wise comply with section 50 (1)(e) or 53, chapter 110, Oregon Laws 2024,
19 provided that the city deliver a notice to Marion County, the Depart-
20 ment of Land Conservation and Development and any special district
21 providing urban services within the city’s urban growth boundary
22 upon receipt of an application.
23 “(c) May demonstrate need under section 52, chapter 110, Oregon
24 Laws 2024, as of the date of the delivery of the notice under paragraph
25 (b) of this subsection.
26 “(d) May approve a site upon receipt of an application without
27 subjecting the site to any of the processes under section 54 (1), chapter
28 110, Oregon Laws 2024.
29 “(e) Is not required to adopt a binding conceptual plan under sec-
30 tion 50 (1)(g), 54 (3) or 55 (2), chapter 110, Oregon Laws 2024, before
HB 4035-A4 2/23/26
