1 adding a site to the city’s urban growth boundary under paragraph (f)
2 of this subsection.
3 “(f) May select a site application that complies with section 54 (2),
4 chapter 110, Oregon Laws 2024, and, following submission under para-
5 graph (h)(A) of this subsection and approval under subsection (2) of
6 this section, add the site to the city’s urban growth boundary.
7 “(g) For a site added under paragraph (f) of this subsection, shall
8 adopt a master plan that, following submission under paragraph (h)(B)
9 of this subsection and approval under subsection (2) of this section,
10 must be applied to the site upon annexation of the site. The master
11 plan must:
12 “(A) Meet any requirements applicable to a conceptual plan under
13 section 55 (3), chapter 110, Oregon Laws 2024; and
14 “(B) Require no fewer than 600 residential units to be developed on
15 the site.
16 “(h) Shall have the city’s site selection reviewed, in lieu of the ap-
17 proval procedures set forth in section 57, chapter 110, Oregon Laws
18 2024, by submitting to the department:
19 “(A) The selected site application and proposed amendment to the
20 city’s urban growth boundary under paragraphs (c) to (f) of this sub-
21 section at least 30 days prior to the adoption of the amendment.
22 “(B) A master plan for the site described in paragraph (g) of this
23 subsection at least 30 days prior to an annexation hearing for any
24 property included in the site.
25 “(i) Shall comply with an order by the department under subsection
26 (2) of this section.
27 “(2)(a) The department shall review the submittals under subsection
28 (1)(h) of this section for compliance with the provisions of sections 49
29 to 59, chapter 110, Oregon Laws 2024, and:
30 “(A) If a submittal substantially complies with the provisions of
