1 sections 49 to 59, chapter 110, Oregon Laws 2024, issue an order ap-
2 proving the submittal; or
3 “(B) If a submittal does not substantially comply with the pro-
4 visions of sections 49 to 59, chapter 110, Oregon Laws 2024, issue an
5 order remanding the submittal to the city with a specific determi-
6 nation of deficiencies in the submittal and with sufficient detail to
7 identify a specific remedy for any deficiency in a subsequent resub-
8 mittal.
9 “(b) The department must issue an order within 30 days of the de-
10 livery of a submittal under subsection (1)(h) of this section.
11 “(c) An order issued by the department under this subsection is
12 subject to appeal as described in section 57 (4), chapter 110, Oregon
13 Laws 2024.
